Brooklyn, while not the glitziest of beaches, has a vibrant seasonal economy. But in Brooklyn, it is often an underground economy, with men and women, many otherwise unemployed, selling everything from home-cooked tamales to bait and tackle on the Boardwalk. Ferrone Malone, 41, is one of the vendors who sells cold drinks on Brighton Beach.

